# Docker Hub Repository for Heart Disease ML

## Docker Image Details

**Repository:** https://hub.docker.com/r/[YOUR_DOCKER_USERNAME]/heart-disease-ml

**Image Tags:**
- `latest` - Latest stable version
- `v[run_id]` - Specific GitHub Actions run version

## Docker Commands

### Pull Image
```bash
docker pull [YOUR_DOCKER_USERNAME]/heart-disease-ml:latest
```

### Run Container
```bash
# Serve MLflow model
docker run -p 5000:5000 [YOUR_DOCKER_USERNAME]/heart-disease-ml:latest

# Interactive mode
docker run -it --rm [YOUR_DOCKER_USERNAME]/heart-disease-ml:latest bash
```

### Build Locally
```bash
# Using MLflow build-docker
cd MLProject
mlflow models build-docker --model-uri runs:/[RUN_ID]/model_random_forest --name heart-disease-ml

# Manual build
docker build -t heart-disease-ml .
```

## Image Contents

- ✅ Python 3.9 environment
- ✅ MLflow with trained models
- ✅ Heart disease prediction models
- ✅ Model serving capabilities
- ✅ All dependencies (pandas, scikit-learn, etc.)

## Usage Examples

### Model Prediction
```bash
# Start container
docker run -p 5000:5000 [YOUR_DOCKER_USERNAME]/heart-disease-ml:latest

# Make prediction (in another terminal)
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/invocations \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"inputs": [[63, 1, 3, 145, 233, 1, 0, 150, 0, 2.3, 0, 0, 1]]}'
```

### Development
```bash
# Mount local directory for development
docker run -it --rm -v $(pwd):/workspace [YOUR_DOCKER_USERNAME]/heart-disease-ml:latest bash
```

